title: Strange Printer II
content: There is a strange printer with the following two special requirements: On each turn, the printer will print a solid rectangular pattern of a single color on the grid. This will cover up the existing colors in the rectangle. Once the printer has used a color for the above operation, the same color cannot be used again. You are given a matrix , where is the color in the position of the grid. Return if it is possible to print the matrix , otherwise, return .
